In my flow-state 🧘🏼‍♀️ 

I’ve always been a bit of a yogi, but I’ve turned to it even more this past year to slow my mind down and be more connected to myself.

There’s been many life changes thrown at me these past 8months that never seem to have an end, but I’ve grown to be more gentle and patient through the process. I’ve gained so much mental clarity through yoga, breath-work and meditation.

We often get caught up in the highlights of people’s lives on social media and forget that they, too, have challenges they’re overcoming. 

Always show kindness, even when you’re having a bad day. You never know the impact you can make 💛

My furever best friend… 🥺🐾 

I never expected to spend my 30th birthday mourning my fur-baby. Things happened so fast and I’m still in shock he’s gone. My baby Louis was 12 years old and full of life. Everyone that met him always said he didn’t act like a “normal dog” and was more a little toddler human attached at your hip. He was the biggest snuggler, lover, active hiker. He loved everyone he came across and touched so many lives. I do not know what life is like without you. I was barely a freshmen in college when I adopted you and we’ve been attached at the hip since. My little Louis… I love and miss you dearly. I hope puppy heaven is full of puppucinos, lamb-lamb toys and table scraps. You were one of a kind 🤍

#fureverfamily #fureverbestfriend #cockapoolove #doggylove #mansbestfriend #doglover #imissyou

Take what is needed, and let go of the rest 🧘🏼‍♀️✨

Do you struggle to let go of things that no longer serve you? 

Try this affirmation: 

✨ I release attachment to other people, substances, and unrealistic ideas that don’t serve me. I honor myself as a cultivate conscious simplicity. I recognize the difference between a “want” and a “need”. ✨

As I am learning all about Yoga and it’s philosophy, this practice of character building has been incredibly eye-opening. The Aparigraha is all about letting go, non-attachment, and non-possession. 

“Take only what is needed, and let things go with ease when they are no longer enhancing vitality” 🧘🏼‍♀️ 🌺 

I invite you to dig deeper and ask yourself: what are you attached to that isn’t serving you? 📖💭

You are exactly where you are supposed to be 🦋
